1
00:00:00,455 --> 00:00:04,122
(three yawns)

2
00:00:05,247 --> 00:00:06,580
Spending their summer vacation

3
00:00:06,664 --> 00:00:10,205
absorbed in a new game...
the three Detective Boys.

4
00:00:10,789 --> 00:00:12,330
At a convenience store,

5
00:00:12,747 --> 00:00:15,497
they happened to meet a boy
from the same Teitan Elementary,

6
00:00:16,330 --> 00:00:19,831
and ended up going to play games
at the home of his relative.

7
00:00:21,622 --> 00:00:24,414
Something about that house
felt off to me,

8
00:00:25,706 --> 00:00:29,747
and then Toshinari found
a gruesome body in the next room.

9
00:00:32,747 --> 00:00:36,372
Meanwhile, between
detectives Sato and Takagi...

10
00:00:37,372 --> 00:00:39,914
It's gone. That thing.

11
00:00:41,914 --> 00:00:44,414
Huh? G-g-gone... you don't mean...

12
00:00:44,831 --> 00:00:48,080
It's embarrassing,
so don't tell anyone.

13
00:00:51,539 --> 00:00:53,580
M-Miwako's having a baby.

14
00:00:53,664 --> 00:00:55,706
Congratulations are in order!

15
00:00:58,163 --> 00:00:59,789
Sun blazing,
undaunted by the heat,

16
00:00:59,872 --> 00:01:01,580
a slick and stylish
deduction show.

17
00:01:01,664 --> 00:01:05,163
Detective Takagi, a papa?
A shocking trick stuns them both.

18
00:01:05,247 --> 00:01:06,789
Seeing through
the one and only truth,

19
00:01:06,872 --> 00:01:08,539
a child in appearance,
a grown-up in mind,

20
00:01:08,622 --> 00:01:10,872
his name is Detective Conan!

21
00:01:14,534 --> 00:01:19,868
♪~

22
00:02:47,826 --> 00:02:53,826
~♪

23
00:02:55,219 --> 00:03:00,419
"Detective Love Story at MPD Headquarters (Truth)"

24
00:03:05,659 --> 00:03:11,409
(detectives murmuring)

25
00:03:25,117 --> 00:03:28,201
(Chiba humming)
Oh?

26
00:03:33,992 --> 00:03:36,701
I'm back. Huh?

27
00:03:39,534 --> 00:03:42,950
Wh-what's with this?
This ominous mood.

28
00:03:44,576 --> 00:03:47,659
Ah, well, the thing is, Chiba...

29
00:03:50,659 --> 00:03:52,534
Here it is, found it.

30
00:03:52,618 --> 00:03:55,618
A boxed lunch
made on August 13th,

31
00:03:55,701 --> 00:03:58,034
and an August 13th newspaper.

32
00:03:58,618 --> 00:04:01,451
Well, I buy a newspaper
every day, so...

33
00:04:01,576 --> 00:04:04,785
But even if you're only
looking after him for a week,

34
00:04:05,409 --> 00:04:09,785
feeding a child nothing but snacks,
convenience store lunches and cup noodles...

35
00:04:10,201 --> 00:04:12,950
shouldn't you think
a little more about his diet?

36
00:04:13,034 --> 00:04:15,034
Noriya's still growing.

37
00:04:16,701 --> 00:04:20,284
S-Sato's showing
a mother's instincts.

38
00:04:20,576 --> 00:04:23,576
And, and the papa is me.

39
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:25,701
Ugh...

40
00:04:25,785 --> 00:04:27,493
Hey, Takagi?
Huh?

41
00:04:27,950 --> 00:04:29,909
Did you go to the store and check?

42
00:04:29,992 --> 00:04:30,992
Oh, yes.

43
00:04:31,534 --> 00:04:34,992
He was clearly caught
on the store's security camera.

44
00:04:35,075 --> 00:04:38,825
Yesterday, August 13th,
around 6 p.m.,

45
00:04:38,909 --> 00:04:41,534
there was Yasutomi,
doing his shopping.

46
00:04:41,950 --> 00:04:45,284
And of course, at the same time,
Toshinari shopping too,

47
00:04:45,367 --> 00:04:47,493
along with Noriya.
Right.

48
00:04:48,034 --> 00:04:51,284
Oh, and one more thing...
near that store,

49
00:04:51,367 --> 00:04:53,659
on the road in front
of that flower shop,

50
00:04:53,743 --> 00:04:56,493
there was a traffic accident
about six months ago.

51
00:04:56,909 --> 00:04:58,784
A traffic accident?
Yes.

52
00:04:59,117 --> 00:05:03,618
Apparently, to avoid a woman
who suddenly ran out into the road,

53
00:05:03,825 --> 00:05:07,909
the driver swerved hard
but couldn't avoid her, hit her,

54
00:05:07,992 --> 00:05:12,784
then crashed into the guardrail
in the oncoming lane and lost consciousness.

55
00:05:13,284 --> 00:05:15,784
Thanks to someone nearby
who called an ambulance,

56
00:05:15,867 --> 00:05:18,784
the driver survived,

57
00:05:18,867 --> 00:05:19,950
but the woman who was hit...

58
00:05:20,034 --> 00:05:24,493
her clothes got caught
and no one noticed she was under the car,

59
00:05:24,576 --> 00:05:28,034
so treatment came too late
and she passed away.

60
00:05:28,743 --> 00:05:33,117
According to the driver,
the woman ran out into the road

61
00:05:33,201 --> 00:05:35,159
as if something
were chasing her.

62
00:05:35,242 --> 00:05:37,950
And? What does that accident

63
00:05:38,034 --> 00:05:39,742
have to do with this murder?

64
00:05:40,242 --> 00:05:43,867
Well, apparently
the store clerk saw it...

65
00:05:43,950 --> 00:05:47,117
Yasutomi running away
from the accident scene.

66
00:05:47,201 --> 00:05:50,284
And the woman who was hit...

67
00:05:50,367 --> 00:05:53,950
Yes. The one who died
in that accident...

68
00:05:54,034 --> 00:05:55,992
was my older sister, Mika.

69
00:05:56,409 --> 00:05:58,242
Ever since the day
of that accident,

70
00:05:58,326 --> 00:06:01,659
I've gone to lay flowers
at the scene every day.

71
00:06:01,909 --> 00:06:03,618
I-I see.

72
00:06:03,701 --> 00:06:06,534
But... as an offering,

73
00:06:06,618 --> 00:06:08,659
those flowers seem
a bit flashy.

74
00:06:08,742 --> 00:06:14,284
My sister loved the color pink,
so I thought flowers like that suit her now and then.

75
00:06:14,367 --> 00:06:16,326
I-I see.

76
00:06:16,409 --> 00:06:18,409
Hey, mister.
Huh?

77
00:06:18,825 --> 00:06:22,451
Did your sister have
any troubles or worries?

78
00:06:22,534 --> 00:06:25,159
Huh?
Like, for example...

79
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:27,909
A stalker?
Huh?

80
00:06:28,493 --> 00:06:29,534
Was there?

81
00:06:30,201 --> 00:06:34,576
No, my sister never mentioned
anything like that to me.

82
00:06:35,034 --> 00:06:36,618
I knew it.

83
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:39,159
The one who killed Yasutomi...

84
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:42,326
is this man, Toshinari Shiga.

85
00:06:42,784 --> 00:06:45,618
But this man has an alibi.

86
00:06:46,242 --> 00:06:51,451
During the time of the crime,
August 13th, from 7 p.m. to 9 p.m., two hours,

87
00:06:51,909 --> 00:06:55,034
he says he was with Noriya
the whole time.

88
00:06:57,326 --> 00:06:59,534
Hey, let's air out
the room a bit.

89
00:06:59,618 --> 00:07:02,825
No way, it's already getting dark.
We have to head home.

90
00:07:03,284 --> 00:07:06,867
Seriously? I already opened
the bag of snacks.

91
00:07:06,950 --> 00:07:09,367
Genta, you're spilling them.

92
00:07:09,451 --> 00:07:10,867
Don't you have a plate or something?

93
00:07:10,950 --> 00:07:13,242
I think there were
some paper ones.

94
00:07:13,534 --> 00:07:16,618
Huh? What happened to your leg?
Huh?

95
00:07:17,117 --> 00:07:19,618
There are marks
like you pinched it.

96
00:07:19,909 --> 00:07:22,618
A-a mosquito bite,
I think I scratched it too much.

97
00:07:26,742 --> 00:07:30,658
Hey, that Yaiba movie
you watched last night... could it be...

98
00:07:32,326 --> 00:07:33,950
Yeah, that's right.

99
00:07:34,034 --> 00:07:36,825
I watched it holding in
my pee the whole time.

100
00:07:38,284 --> 00:07:40,201
If that's the case,
then that newspaper...

101
00:07:40,950 --> 00:07:42,034
Could it be...

102
00:07:43,201 --> 00:07:44,617
C-Conan?

103
00:07:48,159 --> 00:07:49,326
Just as I thought.

104
00:07:50,117 --> 00:07:52,867
Only the August 12th
newspaper is missing.

105
00:07:53,451 --> 00:07:54,950
No doubt about it.

106
00:07:55,742 --> 00:07:57,409
The culprit is this man.

107
00:07:58,242 --> 00:08:00,700
This man bent time

108
00:08:00,784 --> 00:08:03,617
to complete his alibi trick.

109
00:08:05,201 --> 00:08:07,867
Bending even
Noriya's feelings along with it.

110
00:08:09,784 --> 00:08:14,117
Anyway, during the time of the crime,
last night from 7 to 9,

111
00:08:14,742 --> 00:08:17,201
in this room next to
the murder scene,

112
00:08:17,284 --> 00:08:22,742
if Toshinari and Noriya,
who were here the whole time watching a movie on TV,

113
00:08:22,825 --> 00:08:25,034
heard nothing suspicious,

114
00:08:25,575 --> 00:08:29,493
then all we can do is ask
the other residents.

115
00:08:29,575 --> 00:08:34,700
But this apartment is scheduled
for demolition next year,

116
00:08:34,784 --> 00:08:38,534
so the only other residents are
the elderly couple on the second floor,

117
00:08:39,034 --> 00:08:42,493
and last night they were apparently
staying at their grandchild's place.

118
00:08:42,575 --> 00:08:43,617
Is that so?

119
00:08:43,909 --> 00:08:46,992
Hey, Haibara, look after everyone.
Sure.

120
00:08:47,867 --> 00:08:51,159
All right, everyone,
let's stay at the professor's tonight

121
00:08:51,242 --> 00:08:52,534
and play games all night.

122
00:08:52,617 --> 00:08:55,367
Then let's play
"Titan Hunter"!

123
00:08:55,784 --> 00:08:57,534
Yeah, let's!
Then I'll...

124
00:08:57,617 --> 00:08:59,284
go grab the game from my house.

125
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:02,575
Noriya, will you come too?
About the games...

126
00:09:02,658 --> 00:09:04,784
I want to ask you a lot.
Huh?

127
00:09:05,201 --> 00:09:09,284
Besides, you don't want to sleep
next to a room where a murder happened, right?

128
00:09:09,617 --> 00:09:11,034
Y-yeah.

129
00:09:15,451 --> 00:09:16,909
Aren't you going?

130
00:09:16,992 --> 00:09:18,992
Yeah. More importantly...

131
00:09:19,575 --> 00:09:21,493
why would you move into

132
00:09:21,575 --> 00:09:24,075
an apartment that's getting
torn down next year?

133
00:09:24,159 --> 00:09:26,742
I wanted to completely
change the mood.

134
00:09:27,034 --> 00:09:32,159
Before, I lived with my sister,
and she died in a traffic accident.

135
00:09:32,533 --> 00:09:35,493
But you moved in
a month ago, right?

136
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:40,201
Then you'd think you'd buy
pots and pans and all sorts of things,

137
00:09:40,284 --> 00:09:42,451
but there's nothing
in this room.

138
00:09:42,533 --> 00:09:45,992
Ah, I'm bad at cooking,
so no kitchen tools.

139
00:09:46,242 --> 00:09:48,284
But you know,
at the sink...

140
00:09:48,367 --> 00:09:51,451
there's no detergent,
no scrub brush, no sponge,

141
00:09:51,533 --> 00:09:54,201
which means you don't have
any dishes or cups either, right?

142
00:09:55,034 --> 00:09:58,159
Ah, I was planning
to buy more soon.

143
00:09:58,867 --> 00:10:00,575
Oh, is that so.

144
00:10:00,658 --> 00:10:05,242
And here I assumed it was because
the moment you killed your neighbor Yasutomi,

145
00:10:05,326 --> 00:10:07,742
you planned
to move out right away.

146
00:10:23,919 --> 00:10:26,669
W-wait, Conan,
what do you mean?

147
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:31,669
Toshinari was watching TV
during the time of the crime,

148
00:10:31,753 --> 00:10:33,128
last night from 7 to 9.

149
00:10:33,711 --> 00:10:35,419
Together with Noriya.

150
00:10:35,502 --> 00:10:37,419
But Noriya told me...

151
00:10:37,836 --> 00:10:41,669
that while watching the movie,
he held in his pee the whole time.

152
00:10:42,128 --> 00:10:45,419
That means for two hours,

153
00:10:45,502 --> 00:10:48,170
the movie was never
interrupted once, right?

154
00:10:48,253 --> 00:10:49,378
Yeah.

155
00:10:49,961 --> 00:10:52,086
I-I see, a rental DVD.

156
00:10:52,586 --> 00:10:54,003
A rental DVD?

157
00:10:54,086 --> 00:10:56,627
Yes. If it's airing
on TV around now,

158
00:10:57,086 --> 00:11:01,836
then the rental of that movie
must have started, and it'd be on sale too.

159
00:11:02,170 --> 00:11:05,794
I see. He got hold of
that movie in advance,

160
00:11:05,878 --> 00:11:10,253
put it in the player,
and at the right moment, hit play,

161
00:11:10,336 --> 00:11:14,836
making the kid think
it was airing on TV right then.

162
00:11:14,919 --> 00:11:19,502
But Toshinari, on the night
of the crime, August 13th,

163
00:11:19,586 --> 00:11:23,253
besides the movie, you said
you were playing games with Noriya

164
00:11:23,336 --> 00:11:25,753
the whole time, didn't you?
Yes.

165
00:11:25,961 --> 00:11:28,627
Before and after the movie.
I see...

166
00:11:29,627 --> 00:11:32,086
Then the crime
really would be impossible...

167
00:11:32,170 --> 00:11:35,377
Was it really
August 13th?

168
00:11:35,461 --> 00:11:39,794
A-ah, that day,
he had Noriya check

169
00:11:39,878 --> 00:11:42,878
the date on the newspaper
he bought at the store, apparently.

170
00:11:42,961 --> 00:11:43,961
R-right?

171
00:11:44,461 --> 00:11:45,836
Y-yeah.

172
00:11:46,044 --> 00:11:50,419
See, that day was definitely
August 13th.

173
00:11:50,502 --> 00:11:53,377
Oh, my mistake then.

174
00:11:54,128 --> 00:11:58,419
Convenience stores don't sell
tomorrow's future newspaper, after all.

175
00:11:58,669 --> 00:12:00,253
Ah... a tabloid.

176
00:12:00,544 --> 00:12:03,377
Huh?
You mean an evening paper...

177
00:12:03,461 --> 00:12:05,961
those carry
the next day's date.

178
00:12:06,211 --> 00:12:09,753
If he bought one of those
and had Noriya check it,

179
00:12:09,836 --> 00:12:12,253
he could make him
mistake the date.

180
00:12:12,794 --> 00:12:17,711
Come to think of it,
only the August 12th paper was missing.

181
00:12:17,794 --> 00:12:18,794
I see.

182
00:12:19,086 --> 00:12:22,794
The evening paper dated the 13th,
bought on August 12th,

183
00:12:22,878 --> 00:12:24,711
he got rid of it.

184
00:12:24,794 --> 00:12:26,711
In other words, the night
you watched the movie

185
00:12:26,794 --> 00:12:31,044
on TV with Noriya
was August 12th.

186
00:12:31,128 --> 00:12:34,044
On the night of the 13th,
the day after the murder,

187
00:12:34,128 --> 00:12:36,878
there was plenty of time
to commit the crime, wasn't there?

188
00:12:36,961 --> 00:12:38,586
W-wait a minute.

189
00:12:38,961 --> 00:12:40,711
Noriya said it, didn't he?

190
00:12:40,794 --> 00:12:43,669
That he watched the movie
on TV yesterday.

191
00:12:43,753 --> 00:12:47,794
Even a child can tell the difference
between yesterday and the day before, don't you think?

192
00:12:48,170 --> 00:12:52,461
If you don't believe me, call Noriya
back here and ask him.

193
00:12:52,544 --> 00:12:55,502
He'll tell you today is the day
after he watched the movie.

194
00:12:55,586 --> 00:12:57,586
Come to think of it,
Noriya said this.

195
00:12:57,919 --> 00:12:59,627
On August 13th,

196
00:12:59,711 --> 00:13:04,836
in the evening after coming back
from the store, he played games until the movie started,

197
00:13:04,919 --> 00:13:08,836
then after the movie,
played games again until late at night,

198
00:13:08,919 --> 00:13:11,794
woke up early in the morning
and played games,

199
00:13:11,878 --> 00:13:16,294
then around 6 he went with Toshinari
to the store to buy breakfast,

200
00:13:16,377 --> 00:13:20,086
played games again until around noon,
then took a nap,

201
00:13:20,170 --> 00:13:23,878
woke up and played more games,
and since he got hungry,

202
00:13:23,961 --> 00:13:26,794
he went to the store just now
and met us.

203
00:13:27,252 --> 00:13:30,211
Ha. Noriya said that
the whole time he was gaming,

204
00:13:30,294 --> 00:13:32,544
he was always with me,
didn't he?

205
00:13:32,836 --> 00:13:36,836
Yeah. But he said that after
buying and eating breakfast at the store,

206
00:13:36,919 --> 00:13:40,836
you went out
for a little while.

207
00:13:40,919 --> 00:13:43,961
You told him to put on headphones
and play games during that time.

208
00:13:44,044 --> 00:13:47,128
Ah...
Went out? Where?

209
00:13:47,211 --> 00:13:49,711
I-I just stepped outside
for a smoke,

210
00:13:50,128 --> 00:13:52,627
and besides,
that was this morning.

211
00:13:52,711 --> 00:13:55,836
Time-wise, it has nothing
to do with the crime, right?

212
00:13:55,919 --> 00:13:56,961
Speaking of time...

213
00:13:57,502 --> 00:14:00,711
this room doesn't have
a single clock, does it?

214
00:14:01,252 --> 00:14:05,794
The only one who can tell time
is Toshinari, who's wearing a watch.

215
00:14:06,794 --> 00:14:10,711
And, the windows have
thick curtains over them.

216
00:14:11,210 --> 00:14:14,210
If you're gaming the whole time
while eating snacks,

217
00:14:14,294 --> 00:14:19,003
you don't get hungry either,
so you lose track of what time it is, right?

218
00:14:20,669 --> 00:14:23,586
I think you should buy
at least a clock.

219
00:14:23,669 --> 00:14:24,919
Y-yeah.

220
00:14:25,003 --> 00:14:27,753
I see, so this
is what happened.

221
00:14:28,794 --> 00:14:33,753
The day before the crime, August 12th,
you bought an evening paper at the store,

222
00:14:33,836 --> 00:14:37,627
made Noriya think it was the 13th,
and that night,

223
00:14:37,711 --> 00:14:41,086
had him play games
until, say, past 10,

224
00:14:41,169 --> 00:14:45,753
then said it was movie time
and showed him the DVD until around midnight,

225
00:14:45,836 --> 00:14:48,419
then had him play games
until morning,

226
00:14:48,836 --> 00:14:53,836
and said "it's already morning"
to wake him, but it was past noon on the 13th.

227
00:14:53,919 --> 00:14:58,502
You had him game until evening,
then said "let's go buy breakfast,"

228
00:14:58,586 --> 00:15:03,794
and the trip to the store was actually
6 in the evening on the 13th.

229
00:15:03,961 --> 00:15:06,294
I-I see, this time of year,

230
00:15:06,377 --> 00:15:09,794
both 6 a.m. and 6 p.m.
have the sun up and it's bright.

231
00:15:10,377 --> 00:15:13,128
And after he ate
that breakfast,

232
00:15:13,210 --> 00:15:15,294
if you said you were stepping out
and went outside,

233
00:15:16,086 --> 00:15:19,878
you had plenty of opportunity
to kill Yasutomi.

234
00:15:20,169 --> 00:15:22,335
At that time, Noriya
was wearing headphones

235
00:15:22,419 --> 00:15:24,627
and couldn't hear the sounds,
it seems.

236
00:15:25,294 --> 00:15:28,836
After that, you returned
to your own room and again

237
00:15:28,919 --> 00:15:33,003
had Noriya play games
until morning, then urged him to nap,

238
00:15:33,086 --> 00:15:36,711
and let him sleep soundly until noon
today, August 14th.

239
00:15:37,544 --> 00:15:41,586
So to Noriya,
the two days of the 13th and 14th

240
00:15:41,669 --> 00:15:44,961
felt like just a single day.

241
00:15:45,419 --> 00:15:47,669
Well? Anything wrong?

242
00:15:47,878 --> 00:15:52,836
You're Wrong... but why would I kill my neighbor...

243
00:15:52,919 --> 00:15:53,961
Whoa.
Ah!

244
00:15:54,252 --> 00:15:56,961
Your sister sure was
a beauty, Toshinari.

245
00:15:57,210 --> 00:15:58,669
H-hey, kid.

246
00:15:58,919 --> 00:16:00,461
But, that's strange.

247
00:16:00,544 --> 00:16:03,544
In the later photos,
nobody's facing this way,

248
00:16:03,961 --> 00:16:06,836
and there's some kind of
hole at the top.

249
00:16:08,419 --> 00:16:12,252
You really loved
your sister, didn't you?

250
00:16:12,335 --> 00:16:17,127
You had these secretly taken photos
of her lined up and pinned somewhere, right?

251
00:16:17,627 --> 00:16:20,085
Th-that means...
A stalker.

252
00:16:20,169 --> 00:16:21,294
Ah.

253
00:16:22,169 --> 00:16:25,085
Come to think of it,
forensics mentioned something.

254
00:16:25,169 --> 00:16:29,252
In Yasutomi's room too, there was
a board with photos pinned to it,

255
00:16:29,335 --> 00:16:31,961
but most of them were out of line
with the sun-faded marks.

256
00:16:32,252 --> 00:16:34,335
Then, what was pinned
to that board

257
00:16:34,419 --> 00:16:38,586
was really these photos, and after
the crime, to erase the link to yourself,

258
00:16:38,961 --> 00:16:41,335
you peeled them all off
and instead

259
00:16:41,419 --> 00:16:44,335
pinned up Yasutomi's photos
that were in that room.

260
00:16:44,836 --> 00:16:48,461
In that case, the data for these photos
might still remain

261
00:16:48,544 --> 00:16:50,919
on the laptop that was
on Yasutomi's desk.

262
00:16:51,003 --> 00:16:52,544
Check it right away.

263
00:16:52,794 --> 00:16:55,294
It may already be erased, though.
Yes.

264
00:16:55,836 --> 00:16:57,878
It should still be there.
Ah.

265
00:17:00,544 --> 00:17:03,294
I didn't think
that far ahead,

266
00:17:04,127 --> 00:17:07,294
and besides, the reason
I peeled off my sister's photos

267
00:17:07,627 --> 00:17:10,919
was simply that I didn't want
my sister's photos

268
00:17:11,294 --> 00:17:14,586
displayed in that stalker
bastard's room any longer.

269
00:17:14,961 --> 00:17:19,252
Then it really was Yasutomi
who was stalking your sister.

270
00:17:19,669 --> 00:17:20,669
Yes.

271
00:17:21,043 --> 00:17:23,586
I realized it
two months ago.

272
00:17:24,169 --> 00:17:28,544
As usual, while I was laying flowers
at the scene of the accident,

273
00:17:28,919 --> 00:17:31,085
that guy spoke to me.

274
00:17:31,419 --> 00:17:34,085
"Were you a fan of hers too?"
he said.

275
00:17:37,753 --> 00:17:41,961
It bothered me, so I followed him,
and I saw it through the window.

276
00:17:42,544 --> 00:17:46,753
Dozens of my sister's photos
pinned to a board,

277
00:17:47,127 --> 00:17:51,461
and that man muttering,
"It's your fault for running away."

278
00:17:52,753 --> 00:17:55,711
So when your sister
ran out into the road

279
00:17:55,794 --> 00:17:57,794
as if something
were chasing her...

280
00:17:58,210 --> 00:18:01,836
Yes. My sister was
chased by that man,

281
00:18:01,919 --> 00:18:05,586
ran out into the road,
and was hit by the car.

282
00:18:06,294 --> 00:18:11,169
Before I killed that man,
I confirmed it with him directly.

283
00:18:12,294 --> 00:18:15,711
Why did you run away then?
Why didn't you tell the rescue team

284
00:18:15,794 --> 00:18:18,919
that my sister was
under the car?

285
00:18:20,794 --> 00:18:23,502
If you had,
maybe my sister

286
00:18:23,586 --> 00:18:25,836
might still
be alive.

287
00:18:26,377 --> 00:18:30,461
That man just...
just said he was scared.

288
00:18:31,252 --> 00:18:36,960
So you moved in next to Yasutomi's room
and carried out this plan?

289
00:18:37,502 --> 00:18:40,127
Yes. I'd been asked beforehand

290
00:18:40,210 --> 00:18:43,794
to look after Noriya
for a week.

291
00:18:44,002 --> 00:18:46,085
Though I never thought

292
00:18:46,169 --> 00:18:49,294
Noriya would be fooled
this easily.

293
00:18:49,377 --> 00:18:51,252
What are you saying?
Huh?

294
00:18:51,669 --> 00:18:55,669
It worked because Noriya
pinched his own leg, fought off his sleepiness,

295
00:18:55,753 --> 00:18:58,753
and played games
for long hours.

296
00:18:59,169 --> 00:19:01,836
His mother asked him
to stay with you

297
00:19:01,918 --> 00:19:04,794
and cheer you up.

298
00:19:06,252 --> 00:19:09,252
Otherwise, there's no way
a plan like this would work.

299
00:19:10,627 --> 00:19:12,461
Heh. I see.

300
00:19:13,461 --> 00:19:18,335
So the one being looked after
was me, all along.

301
00:19:19,753 --> 00:19:25,753
♪~

302
00:20:33,877 --> 00:20:39,127
~♪

303
00:20:40,043 --> 00:20:43,127
So? What did Noriya say
he's going to do now?

304
00:20:43,210 --> 00:20:48,294
Until his mother comes back,
Professor Agasa will look after him.

305
00:20:48,627 --> 00:20:51,918
For now, the mother told him
over the phone

306
00:20:52,002 --> 00:20:54,544
that Toshinari is going away
on a trip for a while.

307
00:20:54,627 --> 00:20:58,544
I see. ...Now,
won't you tell me already?

308
00:20:59,127 --> 00:21:01,711
Just who were you trying
to give those flowers to?

309
00:21:01,793 --> 00:21:03,918
Why, it's you, obviously, Sato.

310
00:21:04,502 --> 00:21:08,002
Those were actually meant
as a surprise, along with a ring...

311
00:21:08,085 --> 00:21:10,419
I was going to give you
those obedient plant flowers.

312
00:21:11,085 --> 00:21:13,419
A ring and flowers, for me?

313
00:21:13,502 --> 00:21:17,669
Before you give me that, hand over
your red badge, Takagi.

314
00:21:17,753 --> 00:21:22,002
A-a red badge, you mean the one
issued to the First Investigation Division

315
00:21:22,085 --> 00:21:23,377
of the Metropolitan Police,
this one?

316
00:21:23,461 --> 00:21:25,753
But why?

317
00:21:25,835 --> 00:21:27,252
You said you'd
take responsibility...

318
00:21:27,335 --> 00:21:28,918
didn't you?
Huh?

319
00:21:29,544 --> 00:21:32,085
You know, the other day,
when a suspect

320
00:21:32,169 --> 00:21:34,960
you had cuffed
was about to escape,

321
00:21:35,043 --> 00:21:37,419
and I pinned him down
for you, right?

322
00:21:37,502 --> 00:21:41,085
In the scuffle, it seems
I dropped my badge.

323
00:21:42,210 --> 00:21:45,169
Afterward I noticed it was gone
and went back to the scene,

324
00:21:45,252 --> 00:21:48,502
searched all over,
but couldn't find it.

325
00:21:48,586 --> 00:21:52,294
Th-then I picked it up
and put it in my left trouser pocket.

326
00:21:52,502 --> 00:21:54,377
Huh?
Sorry, I forgot to mention it.

327
00:21:54,461 --> 00:21:55,752
No way, seriously?
Whoa.

328
00:21:56,085 --> 00:21:57,377
Hey, hey, Sato.

329
00:21:57,461 --> 00:21:58,586
That's...
Found it.

330
00:21:58,669 --> 00:22:01,461
My red badge.
Thank goodness.

331
00:22:01,752 --> 00:22:06,252
Well, I usually wear it,
but it's fine even without it,

332
00:22:06,335 --> 00:22:10,085
and if I tell the higher-ups,
they'd issue me a new one right away.

333
00:22:10,377 --> 00:22:13,252
Oh, really? Here I assumed

334
00:22:13,335 --> 00:22:15,793
it'd mean a written apology,
and I was so embarrassed,

335
00:22:16,169 --> 00:22:18,918
I've been down about it
this whole time.

336
00:22:19,002 --> 00:22:24,043
U-um, so the thing Sato said
was missing was...

337
00:22:24,127 --> 00:22:26,960
Yep, this red badge.

338
00:22:27,043 --> 00:22:29,793
Phew. Whew, that was close.

339
00:22:32,752 --> 00:22:35,294
Hey, what are you
feeling down about?

340
00:22:38,002 --> 00:22:40,461
We caught the real culprit
in no time,

341
00:22:40,544 --> 00:22:43,544
so straighten up,
straighten up.

342
00:22:43,627 --> 00:22:44,918
Haa.

343
00:22:47,335 --> 00:22:49,377
For a while now,
the two of us...

344
00:22:50,043 --> 00:22:52,085
are being watched,
aren't we?

345
00:22:52,169 --> 00:22:53,627
Miwako.

346
00:22:54,335 --> 00:22:56,210
Yumi, and Chiba too.

347
00:22:56,669 --> 00:23:00,377
Hey, Yumi, everyone's
staring at us.

348
00:23:00,461 --> 00:23:02,544
Ask your own heart.

349
00:23:02,627 --> 00:23:03,627
Huh?

350
00:23:03,710 --> 00:23:05,793
Miwako, I hear
that thing of yours is gone?

351
00:23:06,210 --> 00:23:08,627
Oh, right, right.
I found it.

352
00:23:09,710 --> 00:23:10,918
You found it?

353
00:23:11,127 --> 00:23:14,668
See, Takagi here
had picked it up.

354
00:23:14,752 --> 00:23:18,544
If he'd told me sooner,
I wouldn't have gotten so down about it.

355
00:23:18,627 --> 00:23:19,627
Ah.

356
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:21,668
D-don't tell me...

357
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:24,085
Yeah, yeah.
Huh? What?

358
00:23:24,169 --> 00:23:28,586
(seizing sound)
21:36, Wataru Takagi apprehended.

359
00:23:28,668 --> 00:23:31,002
We will now escort him
to the interrogation room.

360
00:23:31,085 --> 00:23:32,085
Roger.

361
00:23:32,169 --> 00:23:34,835
Huh? Whaaat?

362
00:23:34,918 --> 00:23:36,793
Ah... hey, wait.

363
00:23:37,335 --> 00:23:41,544
Oh boy. Takagi,
you've done something again, haven't you.

364
00:23:42,294 --> 00:23:45,586
Sorry, it's a misunderstanding,
just a little mix-up.

365
00:23:45,668 --> 00:23:50,544
No, the one who's mistaken is me...
Ah, Sato!

366
00:23:51,043 --> 00:23:52,918
Wow, amazing.

367
00:23:58,877 --> 00:24:02,169
Yeah, the two of us
get along really well, but...

368
00:24:04,002 --> 00:24:05,835
All right!
Kyahaha!

369
00:24:06,210 --> 00:24:07,294
Oh no, he's drowning.

370
00:24:09,502 --> 00:24:13,586
Is there something important
captured in this footage?

371
00:24:15,427 --> 00:24:16,927
Next Conan,

372
00:24:16,927 --> 00:24:20,927
"The Man Betrayed by the Sea".

373
00:24:36,227 --> 00:24:39,027
Next Conan's Hint:

374
00:24:39,027 --> 00:24:41,027
"Necklace".

375
00:24:41,064 --> 00:24:42,816
Next week, the broadcast will be on break.

376
00:24:42,858 --> 00:24:43,617
Going somewhere?

377
00:24:43,734 --> 00:24:44,443
Yeah!

378 
00:24:44,730 --> 00:24:46,570
It's for homework, right?
